<<<<<Small Description>>>>> GPU-Accelerated Data Science with cuDF, cuML, cuGraph, and Distributed Dask-CUDA Compute <<<<</Small Description>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Description>>>>> This container provides a GPU-accelerated data science environment built around the RAPIDS ecosystem. It ships with GPU-native dataframes, machine learning, and graph analytics libraries, along with distributed compute support via Dask-CUDA for scaling workloads across multiple GPUs and nodes. JupyterLab is included for interactive development, and the container also runs without a GPU for shell access and lightweight work. No project code is baked in — mount your own code and data at runtime.

Key Features:
- GPU-accelerated dataframes and ETL (cuDF)
- GPU-accelerated machine learning (cuML) and graph analytics (cuGraph)
- Distributed GPU compute via Dask and dask-cuda, including multi-node clusters
- Image and array processing on GPU (cuCIM, CuPy)
- Familiar data science stack (NumPy, Pandas, scikit-learn, XGBoost)
- Visualization and dashboards (Matplotlib, cuxfilter)
- JupyterLab with GPU dashboard extension for interactive development
- InfiniBand-aware networking (UCX) for high-speed multi-node transport <<<<</Description>>>>>
